@NODE arc "Arc Types Supported"

 These are the Arc Types which ArcExtract supports:
 
 
      Full Support:
      
               - Lha = @{ "C:Lha" link lha}
               - Lzx = @{ "C:Lzx or C:UnLzx" link lzx}
               - DMS = @{ "C:DMS or C:UnDMS" link dms}
               - Tgz = @{ "C:Untgz" link tgz}
               - DSQ = @{ "C:PackDev" link dsq}
               
   Partial Support:
                     
               - Zip = @{ "C:UnZip" link zip}
               - Zoo = @{ "C:Zoo" link zoo}
               
               
               
 These are the Arc Types supported by 'Sniffer' mode:
 
 
      Full Support:
      
               - Lha = @{ "C:Lha" link lha}
               - Lzx = @{ "C:Lzx or C:UnLzx" link lzx}
               - DMS = @{ "C:DMS or C:UnDMS" link dms}
               - DSQ = @{ "C:PackDev" link dsq}
               
   Partial Support:
   
               - Zip = @{ "C:UnZip" link zip}            
 
               
               
 If you have any ARrc types or Extracting commands which I haven't listed,
 please send them along to me, I'll be glad to put them in my next version.
  
  
@ENDNODE
                         
@NODE history "History"

 
  v1.0 (17/04/97) - Original Public Release
  
  v1.1 (28/05/97) - Re-Wrote it completely
  
  v1.2 (29/05/97) - Public Release. Fixed MILLIONS of bugs
  
  v1.3 (02/06/97) - Added X and Y positions for the AppIcon, and also added
                    the Appname option. Now has NewIcons support. This means
                    that NewIcons users can now see the MagicWB in the right
                    colours (thx Curt!!).
  
  v1.5 (07/06/97) - New XEN setting. Brand new revolutionary system called
                    'Sniffer' mode. More Console control. Added DSQ support
  
  v1.6 (10/06/97) - Prefs Window now centers on the WB screen. Added a 
                    little bit of support for MagicWB users. Fixed the bug
                    that crashed the system when 2 copies were run.
                    New Status Bar. Last version for a while.
  
@ENDNODE

